The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, July 30: Lupin has acquired German sales and marketing generics firm Hormosan Pharma GmbH. With this acquisition, Lupin will be able to add significant value through its strengths in R amp;D and strong, complementary pipeline leading to major synergies and growth, Lupin chairman Desh Bandhu Gupta said.                            
	 London, July 30: On the back of higher steel prices, ArcelorMittal has posted a more than two-fold jump in net profit at $5.83 billion for the second quarter ended June 30, 2008 against $2.72 billion in the year-ago period.                             
	 Mumbai, July 30: Sebi has hastened the process of an alternative payment system for public issues which will not require retail investors to block their money unless they are allotted shares. In this regard, it has issued circulars to stock exchanges, merchant bankers, registrar and bankers.                            
	 Geneva, July 30: India today blamed the rich nations for their rigid stand on subsidies but said the collapse of global trade talks here should be considered as a pause and not a breakdown of WTO negotiations.                            
	 Calcutta, July 30: A delegation from Indian Chamber of Commerce (ICC) led by Sanjay Budhia and Rajeev Singh met Bengal chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee to discuss how the ICC could partner developmental initiatives of the state government in the future.                                                                                                                          
